# Build context is the repo root. Without these, `COPY packages ./packages` and
# `COPY apps/web ./apps/web` would drag the host's node_modules and build output into
# the image — slow, and host-arch binaries would shadow the ones `npm ci` installs.
node_modules
**/node_modules

dist
**/dist
dist-test
**/dist-test
.next
**/.next

# Must be `**/`-prefixed: a bare `*.tsbuildinfo` matches only the context root. Leaking the
# host's apps/api/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo made `tsc --incremental` believe the build was already
# done, so `nest build` emitted declarations and no .js — and the image crash-looped on a
# missing dist/main.js.
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

.git
.github
.githooks

# Secrets must never enter a build context; .env.example files are fine and are copied
# only if a Dockerfile asks for them.
.env
**/.env
**/.env.local

.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
